article.headline: SMS 58, Indiana State 34
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Deke Thompson scored 12 points to lead Southwest Missouri State to a 58-34 win over Indiana State on Thursday. Southwest Missouri (11-8, 5-6 Missouri Valley Conference) held the Sycamores, the poorest shooting team in the conference with an average of 41 percent from the field, to their lowest point total this season. The Bears led 26-20 at halftime, then opened the second half with an 11-0 run to go up 37-20 with 14:13 left. Indiana State (8-14, 3-8) shot 25 percent (13-of-52) from the floor, including just 4-of-28 (14 percent) in the second half. The Bears forced 20 Indiana State turnovers while shooting 37 percent (20-of-54) from the field. Indiana State went almost the first seven minutes of the second half without scoring, until David Moss made two free throws with 13:22 left. Amani Daanish made the Sycamores' first field goal of the half with 12:48 left. Blake Ahearn and Kellen Easley each scored 11 for Southwest Missouri. Tamarr Maclin added 10. Moss finished with 10 for Indiana State.
